# Honk Stack Rules

## Runtime
- Use `bun <file>` instead of `node <file>` or `ts-node <file>`
- Use `bun test` instead of `jest` or `vitest`
- Use `bun install` instead of `npm install`, `yarn install`, or `pnpm install`
- Use `bun run <script>` instead of `npm run`, `yarn run`, or `pnpm run`
- Use `bunx <package>` instead of `npx <package>`
- Bun automatically loads .env ‚Äî never use dotenv
- Use `Bun.file` over `node:fs` readFile/writeFile
- Use `Bun.$` over execa for shell commands in scripts and CLI code
- Use `bun:sqlite` for SQLite ‚Äî never use better-sqlite3
- Use `WebSocket` built-in ‚Äî never use the `ws` package

## Monorepo
- This is a Turborepo + Bun workspaces monorepo
- Package scope is `@honk/*` ‚Äî replaced with project scope on create
- Packages: `@honk/schemas`, `@honk/core`, `@honk/db`
- Apps: `@honk/server`, `@honk/web`
- Run tasks from the root via turbo ‚Äî never cd into packages to run scripts
- Use `turbo gen` to scaffold new modules ‚Äî never create module files manually

## Architecture
- `@honk/schemas` ‚Äî Zod schemas and inferred types only, no logic
- `@honk/core` ‚Äî pure functions operating on schema types, no framework deps
- `@honk/db` ‚Äî Drizzle client and table definitions only
- `@honk/server` ‚Äî Hono API, imports from schemas + core + db
- `@honk/web` ‚Äî React frontend, imports from schemas + core, type-only import from server

## Dependency rules
- `schemas` imports nothing internal
- `core` imports types from `@honk/schemas` only
- `db` imports nothing internal
- `server` imports from `@honk/schemas`, `@honk/core`, `@honk/db`
- `web` imports from `@honk/schemas`, `@honk/core`, and `AppType` from server as a type-only import
- Never import server runtime code into web ‚Äî type imports only

## Backend
- Use Hono for the HTTP server ‚Äî never Express, Fastify, or Elysia
- Use `@hono/zod-validator` with `zValidator` for request validation
- Use shared Zod schemas from `@honk/schemas` for validation ‚Äî never define schemas inline
- Follow controller ‚Üí service ‚Üí repository pattern strictly
- Controllers handle HTTP only ‚Äî no business logic, no DB access
- Services orchestrate ‚Äî call core functions for business rules, call repository for data
- Repositories handle DB access only ‚Äî return domain types not raw DB rows
- Export `AppType` from `apps/server/src/index.ts` for Hono RPC client

## Drizzle
- Table definitions live in `packages/db/src/schema/`
- Export all tables from `packages/db/src/schema/index.ts`
- Use `InferSelectModel` and `InferInsertModel` for DB row types
- Run `bun db:generate` after schema changes to generate migrations
- Run `bun db:migrate` to apply migrations
- Never write raw SQL ‚Äî use Drizzle query builder

## Frontend
- Use Vite for dev server and builds ‚Äî never Bun.serve for the web app
- Use TanStack Router for routing with file-based routes in `src/routes/`
- Use TanStack Query for server state ‚Äî never fetch directly in components
- Define query options in `*.queries.ts` files ‚Äî share between loaders and components
- Route loaders call `queryClient.ensureQueryData()` to prefetch
- Components use `useSuspenseQuery()` ‚Äî data is always ready, no loading states needed
- Use Hono RPC client from `src/lib/client.ts` ‚Äî never write raw fetch calls
- Import `AppType` from server as a type-only import ‚Äî never import runtime server code
- React Compiler handles memoization ‚Äî never use useMemo, useCallback, or memo manually

## Styling
- Use Panda CSS for all styling ‚Äî never inline styles, plain CSS classes, or Tailwind
- Use `cva` from `styled-system/css` for component variants
- Use `css` from `styled-system/css` for one-off styles
- Use design tokens from `panda.config.ts` ‚Äî never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography
- Use Ark UI for all interactive components ‚Äî dialogs, selects, popovers, menus, tooltips
- Never build custom interactive components from scratch ‚Äî always use Ark UI primitives
- Run `panda codegen` after changing `panda.config.ts`
- Never edit files in `styled-system/` ‚Äî it is auto-generated

## Schemas
- All Zod schemas live in `@honk/schemas`
- Use `.omit()`, `.partial()`, `.pick()`, `.extend()` to derive schemas ‚Äî never duplicate
- Always export inferred types alongside schemas
- Base schema is the source of truth ‚Äî Create and Update schemas derived from it
- Never use `z.any()` or `z.unknown()` without a comment explaining why

## Core
- All business logic functions are pure ‚Äî same input always produces same output
- No framework imports in core ‚Äî no Drizzle, no Hono, no React
- Functions take domain types from `@honk/schemas` as arguments ‚Äî never raw DB rows
- Every exported function in core must have a corresponding test
- Core functions run on both client and server ‚Äî keep them environment agnostic

## Testing
- Use `bun test` ‚Äî never Jest or Vitest
- Import from `bun:test` ‚Äî `import { test, expect, describe, mock } from 'bun:test'`
- core: zero mocking, plain inputs and outputs
- service: mock the repository layer
- controller: mock the service layer
- web components: mock TanStack Query via React Testing Library
- Never snapshot test ‚Äî prefer explicit assertions

## Code generation
- Use `turbo gen` to generate new modules
- Generator templates live in `turbo/generators/templates/`
- Never manually create the boilerplate files that `turbo gen` produces
- After generating a module, add domain-specific fields to the schema and table before anything else

## Code style
- Biome handles formatting and linting ‚Äî never configure ESLint or Prettier
- Single quotes, 2 space indent, trailing commas (es5)
- Prefer `const` over `let`, never `var`
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Prefer async/await over promise chains
- Never use `any` ‚Äî use `unknown` and narrow, or fix the type properly
- Always handle promise rejections ‚Äî never fire and forget without a catch

## Import patterns
- Import directly from module paths ‚Äî never from package root barrels
- `import type { User } from '@honk/schemas/modules/users/user.schema'`
- Not `import type { User } from '@honk/schemas'`
